modules.description: This module implements cache storage operations backed by MariaDB, providing functions to set and retrieve key-value pairs. It supports setting entries with optional values to allow deletion and overwriting existing keys. The module is used to persist cache data in a MariaDB database and integrates with the application lifecycle through service registration.

This module implements cache storage operations backed by PostgreSQL. It provides functions to set and retrieve key-value pairs, where values can be optional to allow deletion, and integrates with the application lifecycle for initialization. It is used to persist cache entries in a PostgreSQL database, ensuring data durability across application restarts.

This module enables caching with key-value storage and expiration, offering direct operations for in-memory caching while integrating with MariaDB and PostgreSQL for persistent storage. The MariaDB submodule supports setting and retrieving entries with optional values for deletion, storing cache data durably in a MariaDB database and initializing as part of the application lifecycle. The PostgreSQL submodule mirrors this functionality for PostgreSQL-backed caches, ensuring cache persistence across restarts. Use cases include session management, query caching, and optimizing repeated computations in web applications using either SQL backend.
